question: Does it work on a PC, tablet, or mobile?
Does all web browsers work?
What‚Äôs difference between Q1A1 mode and classic mode?
What are logic jump and question/page randomization?
Is it possible to respond again if I go to the page during the survey answer?
How can I share/distribute a survey?
Do you provide results data as files?
answer: All screens provide a responsive and optimized screen.
Except for IE Explorer, it usually works on other browsers such as Edge, Chrome, Safari, Samsung browser.

1 Question 1 Answer mode is published by one question in the slide method, so you can focus on one question.
Classic mode has multiple questions in one section. It can be divided into several sections.

Logic jump is a function that moves to a preset question according to the selected answer.
Question/page randomization means that each respondent has a random order to improve the biased response due to the order.
Yes. If it is the same device and browser, you can continue to respond.

We provides URL links, QR codes, social media (Facebook, Twitter, KakaoTalk, etc.) and HTML codes that can be inserted into web pages. Email sending can be checked by email using 3rd parties (Stibee, Mailchimp, GetResponse, etc.). For details, please check the distribution page after logging in.

Insight/summary data is provided as a ppt file.
Response data provides csv, xlsx files or Google spreadsheet integration.

question: If I run out of the number of responses provided, will I no longer receive responses?
What happens if the file upload question exceeds the capacity?
Is it possible to download files of the file upload question at any time even after changing from a paid plan to a free plan?
If my photo album capacity is exceeded, can I upload more photos?
What is the maximum number of responses I can receive per survey?
What is the maximum number of questions to create per survey?
I am using a standard plan, can I change it to a premium plan?
I'm using a premium plan, can I change it to a standard plan?
answer:
In the paid plan, you can continue receiving answers even though the number of responses are exceeded, but cannot access the Create/Share/Result page.
In the free plan, it will no longer receiving answers when it is exceeded.
Excess responses will be deducted from the number of responses that are newly provided due to plan upgrade or subscription extension.

In the paid plan, if the capacity is exceeded, you can continue receiving a certain amount of responses (as determined by the person in charge), but no longer download the file from the result page. In the free plan, if it is exceeded, no longer receive responses.{1}
Please upgrade your plan to use more storage space.

When changing from a paid plan to free, you can download all files up to +7 days from the service expiration date.
In the free plan, you can download up to 15MB in total.
Please upgrade your plan to use a larger storage space, or manage it by deleting unnecessary photos from previous uploaded photos.
You can receive up to 20,000 responses per survey.

Total 200 questions can be created,
but maximum 20 items per section or page

Yes, that is possible.
If the number of days of the standard plan is 25 days per month /180 days or more per year, the subscription period can be changed without extending the subscription period, and the difference is functioned. If you are less than a day, you can change the subscription period to extend the subscription period, and change to a premium plan immediately after payment approval.

It is impossible to change immediately.
If you pay in a standard plan while using the premium, it will automatically change to a standard plan after the premium plan expires.

question: What is the payment method?
Can I get a cash receipt?
answer: We provide card, card number input, and direct deposit method, and the plan will be upgraded after payment is approved.

For card payment, we issue a purchase slip, cash receipts will be issued for payment by bank transfer.
It takes one more business day from the payment date.
